Lets embed some r code

Well write an R chunk that loads tidyverse package then reads in the Gapminder data set from the data subdirectory of the project

CMD + OPT + i to insert r chunk highlight string then type quotes to add quotes at start and end cmd shit K knitr shortcut toc created via our hashtag headings listed (toc depth = num of #)

Our First Plot

showing gdp per capita on X & life expectancy on Y

gm %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point()

Life Expectancy V. GDP

A Better Plot

gm %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = continent)) +
  scale_x_log10()

Life Expectancy V. GDP

Possible chunk options

Options include: - echo (defaults TRUE) whether to include code in output - results - hide will hide results - hold holds all results until end of r chunk - include(defaults TRUE) if FALSE code wont be run - fig.width, fig.height set dimensions in output - cache (deafults FALSE) if TRUE saves result from R chunk
